y and accessibility for people with disabilities. This global event, celebrated annually, brings together communities, businesses, and organisations to raise awareness and advocate for positive change. In this blog, we'll delve into the significance of Disabled Access Day, its impact on learners, and how various organisations, including The Mandatory Training Group, support this important initiative.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2346_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2347_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2348_">Understanding disabled access</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/inspireinclusion-international-womens-day-multiet-2024-01-09-01-12-04-utc_1.jpg?v=1710243624" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/inspireinclusion-international-womens-day-multiet-2024-01-09-01-12-04-utc_1.jpg?v=1710243624 1536w" width="1000" height="705" alt="Empowering Accessibility: Celebrating Disabled Access Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Empowering Accessibility: Celebrating Disabled Access Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2350_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2351_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Sangiao_photography via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2353_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Disabled access refers to the provision of facilities and services that enable people with disabilities to navigate and participate fully in society. This includes physical accommodations such as ramps, elevators, and accessible toilets, as well as inclusive policies and practices.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2355_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2356_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2357_">Key facts and statistics</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_de0e57cd-a4f8-47de-9af6-73092bf2ab0b.jpg?v=1710236082" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_de0e57cd-a4f8-47de-9af6-73092bf2ab0b.jpg?v=1710236082 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Inclusive Excellence: Enhancing Accessibility Awareness - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Inclusive Excellence: Enhancing Accessibility Awareness - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2359_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2360_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mohdizzuanbinroslan via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-2362_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2363_">According to the World Health Organisation (WHO), approximately 15% of the world's population lives with some form of disability.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2365_">In the UK alone, there are over 13 million disabled people, representing nearly 20% of the population.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2367_">Despite legal requirements for accessibility, many venues and public spaces still lack adequate accommodations for people with disabilities.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2369_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2370_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2371_">How Disabled Access Day empowers learners</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/two-disabled-friends-give-fist-bump-as-a-sign-of-f-2023-11-27-04-57-18-utc.jpg?v=1710245151" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/two-disabled-friends-give-fist-bump-as-a-sign-of-f-2023-11-27-04-57-18-utc.jpg?v=1710245151 1536w" width="1000" height="622" alt="Breaking Barriers: Promoting Disability Rights on Disabled Access Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Breaking Barriers: Promoting Disability Rights on Disabled Access Day - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2373_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2374_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by zamrznutitonovi via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-2376_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2377_"><b>Raising awareness</b> - Disabled Access Day raises awareness among learners about the challenges faced by people with disabilities in accessing public spaces and services. By participating in events and activities, learners gain firsthand experience and empathy for the barriers encountered by others.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2379_"><b>Promoting inclusivity</b> - By celebrating Disabled Access Day, educational institutions can promote inclusivity and diversity within their communities. They can organise events, workshops, and discussions to educate students about accessibility issues and inspire them to become advocates for change.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2381_"><b>Encouraging action</b> - Disabled Access Day encourages learners to take action by advocating for greater accessibility in their schools, workplaces, and communities. By working together and raising their voices, learners can contribute to positive change and create a more inclusive society for all.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2383_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2384_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2385_">Recommendations</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/inclusive-diverse-business-team-brainstorming-idea-2023-11-27-05-15-16-utc.jpg?v=1710243966" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/inclusive-diverse-business-team-brainstorming-idea-2023-11-27-05-15-16-utc.jpg?v=1710243966 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Accessible Facilities: Creating an Inclusive Environment - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Accessible Facilities: Creating an Inclusive Environment - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2387_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2388_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by seventyfourimages via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2390_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As we celebrate Disabled Access Day, let's commit to promoting inclusivity and accessibility in all aspects of our lives. Here are some recommendations for supporting this importan